CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "I'm Going To Win The Nomination - William P. Young, center, Republican candidate for City Council, assures a group of his workers that he has no doubts about being nominated-and good chances to win in November. Listening to the "pep-talk" are, left to right; Mrs. Lula Reis, MRs. Hallie Brown, Mrs. Charlotte Francis, Mrs. Virginia Day, Mrs. Marthera Lunsford, Mrs. Anna McDouglass, Mrs. Mackey Wade. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Lula Reis, Hallie Brown, Charlotte Francis, William P. Young, Virginia Day, Marthera Lunsford, Anna McDouglass, and Mrs. Mackey Wade, standing on sidewalk in front of small lawn with wire fence and wood garage with political posters including "Democrats vote for Henry Ryan for Alderman and Frank M. Varuolo for Constable," during 1955 primary elections
